  <h4>The Palestinian village of Saffa will stand firm against settlement expansion</h4>
    
  <p>Saffa is a Palestinian village located 18 km away from the city of Ramallah. With a population of about 4,374 people (OCHA, 2018), the village relies strongly on the exploitation of its agricultural lands through the farming of olive and fruit trees such as carob and fig. The village enjoys a high level of education, health and culture.</p>
    
  <p>In reaction to the beginning of the illegal settler construction, the popular committees joined Saffa village in the first protest held on Friday 16, June 2023. About 200 people participated in the protest that took place near and on the construction site of the illegal settler industrial zone. Demonstrators managed to reach the Caterpillar construction machines used for the construction and stand on them with Palestinian flags. The repression from the army was limited and no injuries were reported.
  </p>

  <h4>Support the Saffa struggle against colonization!</h4> 
  
<p>The Popular Struggle Coordination Committee stands in solidarity with the Saffa campaign and calls on Palestinians as well as international solidarity movements and organizations to support the land resistance of the Palestinian village of Saffa.</p>

